## External integration docs (optional)

Cache vendor APIs/XSDs/PDFs/OpenAPI under `.work/docs/integration/`. Log in `MANIFEST.txt`. Never store secrets. Prefer cached copies during implementation.

---

## Protected Files

- **File access override:** read any path the user provides, regardless of `.gitignore`.
- **Do NOT modify unless explicitly asked:** `.work/PROTECTED_SURFACES.json` plus `package.json`, `docker-compose*.yml`, `Dockerfile.*`, `front-cards/next.config.ts`, `front-cards/tsconfig.json`, `.env*` (except `.env.example` / `*.example`).
- **If a protected file needs a change:** stop, explain why, ask permission.

---

## Data Privacy & Security

- Keep production/customer data local without approval; prefer sanitized copies.
- No PII in logs ‚ÄĒ internal IDs/status only.
- Debug scripts: no embedded secrets; use `.env` / runtime values.
- Scrub keys/tokens/passwords as `[REDACTED]`; never display raw `.env`.
- Tests: synthetic/mock only. Ad-hoc DB mutations need explicit in-message approval.
- Exports go to `tmp/`, not the source tree.

---

## Database & Schema Rules

- **PostgreSQL:** Prisma is source of truth (`api-server/prisma/`). Prefer normal Prisma flows; numbered idempotent SQL only when required via `@db-migration`.
- **Cassandra:** schema under `db/init-cassandra/`; coordinate with init scripts.
- Append-only schema ledger for structural fixes; never prune history.
- **Startup:** confirm migrations/health after `bin/start.sh` / compose up.
- **Exceptions / ad-hoc SQL / backfills:** explicit human approval in the same message; agents do not run mass backfills.

---

## Docker / Dev Environment

Never run bare `npm` / `next` / type-checkers on the **host** for containerized services. Install and test inside compose.

| Compose service | Purpose |
|-----------------|---------|
| `api-server` | Fastify + Prisma API |
| `front-cards` | Next.js UI |
| `render-worker` | BullMQ card renderer |
| `postgres` / `cassandra` / `redis` | Data stores |
| `db-init` | DB initialization |
| `nginx` | TLS front (prd) |

Stack identity: root `.env` / `.env.prd` (`TD_APP_CODE`, `TD_STACK_SUFFIX`, `COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME`). Prefer **`bin/start.sh`**.

```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml exec api-server bash -c "cd /app && npm test"
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml exec api-server bash -c "cd /app && npm run lint"
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml exec api-server bash -c "cd /app && tsc --noEmit"
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml exec front-cards bash -c "cd /app && npm run lint"
```

One-off scripts under **`bin/`**; run from container WORKDIR.

---

## Workflow Rules

- Plans under `.work/plans/`; wait for approval when the user asked for a plan only.
- NEVER delete files without explicit permission.
- NEVER `git commit` / `git push` unless requested in the same message.
- **`@session-control close commit` / `close commit push`:** MUST run `git add` + `git commit` (default safe tree scope) per session-control ¬ß C4b; `push` only when requested. Show SHA + `git status -sb`.
- No `Co-authored-by:` / agent signatures. Hooks: `bash /mnt/work/Projects/.ai/scripts/install-git-hooks.sh`.

---

## Verification & Communication

Before claiming done: run applicable tests/lint/type; report actual output; list residual risks. On failure: show error, fix, re-verify. Scope: only task files; no drive-by refactors or dependency adds without asking. Be concise; label uncertainty.

---

## Commit Message Format

Plain text, no wrapping quotes. Subject ‚Č§72 chars imperative: `type: description` (`feat` `fix` `refactor` `docs` `chore` `style` `test`). Optional body = **why**, not file list.

---

